5:
Kuzunoha the Golden, She of Nine 
Tails!
8:
Your humble servant Shirano requests 
an audience.
12:
How have you fared since last we 
spoke?
17:
I see you have taken a liking to that 
form.
19:
Hah! It is easy to imitate, if nothing 
else. I could hardly wander about in 
my true form, now could I?
20:
More importantly, tell me of the world 
wanderers.
22:
Yes, Milady. I have yet to see anything 
of significance. I'm afraid I have no 
leads on the girl who summoned 
Orochi.
24:
However, I suspect the mortals will 
cross paths with her again in time.
26:
Very well. Have you any other news to 
report?
30:
Alk has mastered the basic uses of 
soy sauce, so I feel he is ready for 
intermediate techniques.
36:
Oh! Nothing to trouble you with, 
Milady. I've nothing serious to report 
at the moment.
40:
...You wish to adventure with them as 
Inaho has, do you not? 
Shirano, I would give you my leave, 
should you request it.
44:
Your leave! I wouldn't dream of it 
Milady!
47:
We yokai are long-lived, but not 
eternal. For what are we, if not 
mysteries of the night?
48:
When brought to light, we will be no 
more than beasts. Destiny determines 
your destination, but none shall 
decide your path.
49:
Spend your days as you will. 
You may fraternize with the humans, 
if you so wish.
56:
Goodness, you sound like a child! 
I know that lonely little face! 
You needn't worry; I won't abandon 
you.
59: You always were a clingy one, dearie.
62: And YOU are ever the governess...
66:
But of course! SOMEONE has to take 
care of you and the princess!
69:
...You have grown attached to the 
mortals, though. Do you not wish to 
be with them?
71:
What's the harm in few more children 
to supervise?
73:
They're as bad as the princess, Milady. 
Who knows what trouble they'd stick 
their noses into?
75:
Why, their adventures may even lead 
them to you!
78:
Very well, Shirano. Please continue 
keeping tabs on them for me.
81:
Gladly, Milady. You just leave 
everything to me, now!
93:
Great timing! I actually wanted to ask 
you something about that bonito dish 
you assigned me.
97:
In time, dearie, in time. Would you 
both kneel down for a moment?
110:
Yes, yes, now I can reach.
I'm so proud of you both. I've got big expectations for you two!
113: Now then, I must get to work!
117:
W-what was that? She ruffled our hair 
and left just like that... Did you do 
something, Stella?
120: I don't think so... Did you?
